s:352:"<p>Use similar triangles to explain why the slope m is the same between any two distinct points on a non-vertical line in the coordinate plane; derive the equation y = mx for a line through the origin and the equation <i>y</i> = <i>mx</i> + <i>b</i> for a line intercepting the vertical axis at <i>b</i>.</p><p><strong>Grade levels</strong><br />08</p>";